title: Improve ingestion MR job completion time.
body:
For 12GB input data containing 8000 files, there are 8000 mappers because of TextInputFormat and its a overhead. The two MR jobs take around a day to complete. 

CombineTextInputFormat instead of TextInputFormat combines multiple splits for a single mapper and reduces the strain on hadoop platform. It greatly improves job completion time as there are fewer number of mappers to bookkeep.

mapreduce.input.fileinputformat.split.maxsize controls amount of data given to a single mapper. Ex: setting it to 67,108,864 (64M) will create a single mapper for 64M of data (hence multiple input files).

title: ObjectColumnSelector/JS aggregator support for multi-valued columns.
body:
~~You may notice that one of the tests detects the array by using `typeof a !== 'string'` instead of `Arrays.isArray(a)` or `typeof a === 'array'`. This is because the latter two methods don't work. The type of "a" is actually "object" even though it behaves like an array (subscripting and indexOf both work). I don't know why...~~

Xavier found out that Context.newArray makes better arrays than Context.javaToJS, so this does that now.

PS, the `cx.getWrapFactory().setJavaPrimitiveWrap(false)` business causes the strings inside the array to get treated as actual JS strings. Otherwise they get treated as wrapped Java objects and you can't actually compare them to real JS strings.
